citeinfo.origin: Commonwealth of Virginia, Department of Transportation
citeinfo.title: State Mile Marker Signs

pubinfo.publish: ITD / GIS Program, Virginia Department of Transportation

descript.abstract: The locations of state mile marker signs on interstates and primary routes are important sources for various traffic studies as well as information for travelers. This GIS layer displays the locations and corresponding information of state mile marker signs.
descript.purpose: The purpose of this data set is to provide a geographic representation of the location of each state mile marker sign in the Commonwealth, and is to be used in a number of other products and projects.
descript.supplinf: The locations of state mile marker signs on interstates and some primary routes came from GPS latitude and longitude measured by Roadware. The original data collection process was performed for the Maintenance Division's pavement condition data collection. After TED conducted the QA/QC of this data set, it has been adapted for use by the ITD/GIS Program Office, Virginia Department of Transportation.

dataqual.logic: This GIS layer displays the locations and corresponding information of state mile marker signs.
dataqual.complete: Most interstates and some of primary route mile marker signs in the Commonwealth of Virginia are included. There are 11,287 state mile marker signs in this GIS layer.

horizpa.horizpar: The associated quality of mile marker sign locations solely depends on ROADWARE's GPS measurement accuracy (Potential GPS Error). The horizontal positional accuracy meets 1:24,000 national map accuracy standards.

procstep.procdesc: A shape file was received by the ITD / GIS Program from VDOT's Traffic Engineering Division (TED). The data was loaded into SDE for use in the GIS Integrator. Metadata was prepared by the TED and reviewed by a GIS analyst.
